<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}-{5}{y}={43}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}=-{57}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{5}{y}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={43}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{43}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{\left(\frac{{{43}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}\right)}+{9}{y}=-{57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{5}}{{-{{1}}}}\cdot{\left({43}\right)}--\frac{{5}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{215}-{\left({25}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{57}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{57}-{215}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{272}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({25}+{\left({9}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{272}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{34}{y}=-{272}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{272}}{{34}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{5}{\left(-{8}\right)}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{\left({40}\right)}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={43}-{\left({40}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{3}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

